 <tr>
  <td>
   
   <font class="ArticleSource"><big>Spell Changes:</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleHead"><big>Recent Updates</big></font>
   <font class="ArticleAuthorLight">&nbsp;filed by </font><font class="ArticleAuthor">Onetree Tallbarque</font>
   <div align="right">
   <font class="ArticleTime">10/14/2002 12:48 AM CDT &nbsp;&nbsp; 2 Comments</font>
   <div align="left">
   <font class="ArticleText">CHANGE: A bunch of Cold resist buffs (ie. Resist/Endure Cold, Aura of White Petals) were nerfed severely. Fortunately, Circle of Seaons (CoS) was spared. But Aura of White Petals (effect seen on PoM and VT items) was reduced from +50 CR to a measly +10 CR! That's just got to be a bug. All the other Auras of (something) Petals increase buffs by 50.<p>NEW: SHM/63 Tnarg's Mending heals a single target of 1300 points of damage. It costs 450 mana and takes only 3.75 seconds to cast, with no recast time. This is a fast, long range, powerful heal. Great for spot healing.<p>NEW: SHM/64 Khura's Mending heals a single target of 3120 (75% max) points of damage. It costs 600 mana and, like CH, takes 10 seconds to cast, with no recast time. But it has half the range of Tnarg's Mending. So even though they are &quot;mending&quot; spells they are quite different.<p>NEW: DRU/64 Karana's Renewal (KR) heals a single target of 4680 (75% max) points of damage. Like Khura's Mending it costs 600 mana and takes 10 seconds to cast, again with no recast time. Both Khura's Mending and Karana's Renewal have range 100.<p>NEW: DRU/63 Protection of the Nine (PotN) appears to be the single target PotC upgrade Druid's have been looking for. It costs 725 mana.<p>NEW: ENC/62 Glory of Battle (GoB) is a 42 minute single-target VoG upgrade that I'm sure melees will appreciate. It costs 350 mana.<p>NEW: ENC/65 Brotherhood of Battle (BoB) appears to be GoB for groups. It costs double GoB's: 700 mana.<p>NEW: SHM/62 Focus of the Soul (FotS) is a new spell in the Shaman Focus line.<p>NEW: MAG/62 Burnout V allows mages to really make their pets go berzerk.<p>NEW: MAG/64 DRU/65 Destroy Summoned is a summoned-specific nuke for 1200 damage. The target can resist it (ResistAdjust -100).<p>NEW: MAG/64 Planar Renewal gives mages the ability to heal their pets of 900 damage and remove 10 disease counters. It costs 400 mana.<p>CHANGE: It looks like the second generation of some complicated new stacking code has just gone in. An example of this can be seen in the changes to Aegolism:<p>10-13 05:30 Added Slot 5: Stacking2 v2 203: Max Hitpoints(1100)<br>10-13 05:30 Changed Slot 1 from &quot;Stacking1 v1 5: 1100&quot; to &quot;Stacking1 v2 203: Max Hitpoints(1100)&quot;<p>Note the &quot;v2&quot; part. Lots of spells were similarly affected, but mostly priest class. Some spells simply lost their v1 entry.<p>CHANGE: Rangers will get Regrowth at 64, not 63.<p>NEW: I'm sure Rangers will be happy to learn they get Engulfing Roots (DRU/49) at 63.<p>CHANGE: Shadowknights will get Ignite Blood at 61, not 62.<p>CHANGE: Mages will get Xegony's Phantasmal Guard at 62, not 63.<p>CHANGE: Illusion Froglok will fizzle a lot less. Let's hear it from the chanter community. &quot;FROOOAAAK! Oops, pardon me.&quot;<p>NEW: And, finally, Moss Venom (http://lucy.fnord.net/spell.html?id=3158&amp;source=Test) was introduced. No doubt for some level 60+ moss snake. :p<p>CHANGE: DRU/PA Wrath of the Wild can be single-targeted now. Who wants a 350, 500 or 650 damage shield (depending on PA level) that lasts 36 minutes? :)<p>CHANGE: DRU/PA Spirit of the Wood now increases hps 200, 225 or 250 per tick depending on PA level. (It used to be 75, 100 or 125 per tick.) This is in addition to its 55 ds and 48 AC boost. Still lasts 5 ticks. So, at level 3 that's a 1250 heal over 30 seconds.<p>CHANGE: DRU/62 Fury of Ro had its mana cost reduced to 320 from 350.<p>CHANGE: Druids will have to wait till level 64 to cast Protection of the Seasons. Used to be level 63.<p>CHANGE: Druids will get Shield of Bracken at level 65, not 64.<p>CHANGE: DRU/63 Nature's Infusion had its casting time increased from 3.5s to 3.8s, its mana cost increased from 450 to 500, and the amount it heals increased from 1380 to 1750.<p>CHANGE: DRU/63 Swarming Death had its mana cost reduced from 370 to 350 mana.</font>
  </td>
 </tr>
</table>
